<p>I&#8230;am not sure what you mean by this.</p>
<p>EDIT: I edited out the listusers module, because yes, that made no sense.</p>
<p>As for your other concerns, that actually makes less sense than it sounds at first glance. The implication by clicking on &quot;verifying credentials&quot; is that you, the reader (who are in the shoes of O5-6), are clicking submit. I could certainly have added a bunch of filler, and have you click on 1-3 collapsible to show that something is &quot;happening&quot;, but that's not really the point of this.</p>
<p>This is the last time they ran the remote authorization program, by accessing this file. They fucked up, and it locked. Kaboom, the Marshmallow Alligator invasion begins.</p>
<p>Frankly, I think adding a ton of set up, a la a mainlister for urgency would have taken away, and made it more &quot;oh, isn't that unfortunate&quot; than funny.</p>
<p>The punchline is a subversion of expectations, not a complex story. I can understand why that wouldn't work if you were expecting something more involved, however.</p>

